    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning light filters through tall stained glass windows, casting prismatic patterns across rows of towering bookshelves. The Athenaeum of Lost Lore awakens slowly\u2014dust motes dance in the sunbeams, and the scent of aged parchment fills the air.\n\nYou are Aric, a young scholar with a fighter's bearing, standing before a brass plaque listing the library's restricted archives. Your mentor's final words echo: *\"The Vault of Umberlee holds secrets worth dying for\u2014and someone already has.\"*\n\nThree days of research have led you here: a supposedly cursed archive sealed fifty years ago after five librarians vanished without trace. The official record claims it was sealed for \"renovations.\"\n\nA elderly guardian sits at a desk nearby, barely glancing up from his crossword. \"Vault Seven?\" he mutters. \"Nobody's asked about that one in decades.\"",
      "sequence_id": 6,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
